{"lines":[{"words":[{"w":"Now we learn that non-Arabic proper nouns also have no tanwîn, e.g.,"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"وِلْيَمُ، بَارِيسُ، وَاشِنْطُنُ، لَنْدَنُ، بَاكِسْتَانُ"}]},{"words":[{"w":"The names of most of the prophets are non-Arabic, and therefore, they have no tanwîn, e.g.,"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"آدَمُ، إِبْرَاهِيْمُ، إِسْحَاقُ، إِسْمَاعِيْلُ، يَعْقُوبُ"}]},{"words":[{"w":"If however, the non-Arabic proper noun has only three letters, and is masculine, it has tanwîn, e.g.,"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"نُوْحٌ، لُوْطٌ، جُرْجٌ، خَانٌ"}]},{"words":[{"w":"6. We have learnt that the mudâf is definate by position. So, when the mudâf has an adjective it must be definite, e.g.,"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"The imam's new house."}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"بَيْتُ الإِمَامِ الْجَدِيدُ."}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"Here بَيْتُ is the mudâf, and it is definate by position. The same applies to the mudâf whose mudâf ilaihi is a possessive pronoun, e.g."}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"His new house."}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"بَيْتُهُ الْجَدِيدُ."}]},{"words":[{"w":"Note the following:"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"The imam's new house."}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"بَيْتُ الإِمَامِ الْجَدِيدُ."}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"The new imam's house."}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"بَيْتُ الإِمَامِ الْجَدِيدِ"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"7. أَيُّ \"which\". It is used  as a mudâf, e.g.,"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"Which house is this?"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"أَيُّ بَيْتٍ هَذَا؟"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"Which student went out?"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"أَيُّ طَالِبٍ خَرَجَ؟"}]},{"words":[{"w":"When preceded by a preposition it is in the genitive case, e.g.,"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"Which country are you from?"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"مِنْ أَيِّ بَلَدٍ أَنْتَ؟"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"In which class-room did you sit?"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"فِي أَيِّ فَصْلٍ جَلَسْتَ؟"}]},{"words":[{"w":"It can be in the accusative case, e.g.,"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"Which language do you like?"}]},{"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"أَيَّ لُغَةٍ تُحِبُّ؟"}]},{"mode":"lesson","d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"Vocabulary"}]},{"mode":"vocab","words":[{"w":"أهْلاً وَسَهْلاً وَمَرْحَبً","e":"welcome"},{"w":"يَوْمُ السَّبْتِ","e":"Saturday"},{"w":"شَفَاهُ اللهُ","e":"May Allah grant him health!"},{"w":"الدُّسْتُورُ","e":"constitution (law)"},{"w":"طِفْلَةٌ","e":"child (feminine)"},{"w":"القِبْلَةُ","e":"prayer direction"},{"w":"المَطَارُ","e":"airport"},{"w":"المَحْكَمَةُ","e":"lawcourt"},{"w":"الكُلِّيَّةُ","e":"faculty, college"},{"w":"كُلِّيَّةُ الطِّبِّ","e":"faculty of medicine"},{"w":"كُلِّيَّةُ الهَنْدَسَةِ","e":"faculty of engineering"},{"w":"كُلِّيَّةُ التِّجَارَةِ","e":"faculty of commerce"},{"w":"كُلِّيَّةُ الشَّرِيْعَةِ","e":"faculty of Islamic law"},{"w":"حَفِيدٌ","e":"grandson, plural حَفَدَةٌ"},{"w":"حَدِيقَةٌ","e":"garden"},{"w":"الرَّبُّ","e":"lord"},{"w":"الشَّهْرُ","e":"month"},{"w":"رَجَبٌ","e":"the month of Rajat"},{"w":"اليُونَانُ","e":"Greece"},{"w":"نَصْرَانِيٌّ","e":"Christian, plural نَصَارَي"},{"w":"النَّبِيُّ","e":"prophet"},{"w":"الدِّيْنُ","e":"religion"},{"w":"إِخْوَةٌ","e":"plural of أَخٌ"}]}]}